main event: Two round bright white objects resembling stars were observed in the Pacific Ocean.
interesting points: The objects were stationary until suddenly the direction changed, and they moved rapidly and disappeared.
The objects were about the size of stars and had no trail, trail or oscillating motion.
The duration of the sighting was brief, but the essential data like direction, elevation, apparent size, and time of observation were not reported.
The observation was relayed from the West Port Coast Guard Station to Hassle AFS, who then called the Wing Command Post.
Weather conditions included a broken cloud ceiling at 2,399 feet, 3-5 miles visibility, and no thunderstorm activity.
sighted object: two round bright white objects resembling stars
